<strong>The magma scoop</strong>

A closed crucible-to-crucible courier for molten metal. The <strong>only</strong> way to move melt between crucibles.

<strong>Use</strong>
• Empty scoop, right-click a <a href="crucible">crucible</a> with molten contents — scoop fills with that metal.
• Loaded scoop, right-click another crucible — scoop empties into the destination.
• Cross-metal mixing is refused: cannot deposit mithril into an adamantite-loaded crucible.

<strong>Refused</strong>
• World lava (cannot scoop world lava blocks).
• Spilling on the ground, in water, in air (the molten liquid has no spill behavior).
• Any non-crucible block as a target.

<strong>Placement</strong>
Sneak + right-click to place the scoop as a block; it then behaves as a normal storage container.

<strong>Also part of</strong>
The <a href="superheater">superheater</a> recipe uses a magma scoop at its center.
